// NEGATIVE TEST — must NOT compile with --auto-discharge=disable.
//
// A verified `connect` hands back a `*Tls<open!>` connection: the SSL object,
// its SSL_CTX, and the socket must all be freed, and that is a single `open!`
// obligation discharged by `close`. Here the connection is bound to `_` and
// discarded — no `close` ever runs — so the free-chain would leak.
//
// As in the curl lift, the compiler's default auto-discharge pass is clever
// enough to insert the missing `close` for the naive single-disposer case, so
// under DEFAULT settings this compiles. Disable that safety net to lay the
// obligation bare (same flag koru's own suite uses for this class of test):
//
//   koruc run openssl/tests/negative/forgotten_close.kz --auto-discharge=disable
//     -> error[KORU030]: Resource '_' <open!> was not discharged. Call: koru.openssl:close

~import koru/openssl

~koru/openssl:connect(host: "example.com", port: 443)
| ok _ |> _
| err _ |> _
